'''John Dunivant''' is an artist based in Detroit. He wrote and illustrated the short story "[[Wanderer of Worlds]]," which was published in [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 9|''Star Wars Galaxy Magazine'' 9]]. The story showcased the [[Eirrauc]] species, which Dunivant created and designed. Dunviant is best known as the founder, organizer, and lead artist of Theatre Bizarre, an immersive Halloween party held since 2000&mdash;at first illegally on vacant lots, then, after the city intervened, in Detroit's Masonic Lodge.<ref name="MetroTimes1">{{WebCite| url=https://www.metrotimes.com/news/detroits-theatre-bizarre-2023-is-canceled-33673790 |text=Detroit's Theatre Bizarre 2023 is canceled |work=Detroit Metro Times |author=Lee DeVito |date=2023-06-21 |archivedate=20230723063821}}</ref> He cites ''Star Wars'' as a major inspiration for the festival's world-building and mythological aspects.<ref name="MetroTimes2">{{WebCite| url=https://www.metrotimes.com/arts/20-years-ago-what-we-now-call-theatre-bizarre-got-kicked-out-of-the-russell-industrial-center-today-its-detroits-biggest-freak-show-22861116 |text=20 years ago, what is now Theatre Bizarre got kicked out of the Russell Industrial Center — today, it's Detroit's biggest freak show |work=Detroit Metro Times |author=Jeff Milo |date=2019-10-09 |archivedate=20230128174023}}</ref>

